insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-07T04:30:00.000Z', 'tour', 'Tour Diary Friday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
A student who had never held a mic opened for 3,000 people.
What building a youth movement teaches you about business:', 'Everything I know about product-market fit I learned watching a school field at 7am become a festival by noon. Lesson one: distribution beats talent alone — the stage matters because PPP TV cameras are on it. Lesson two: trust is the moat — teachers let us in because we run mentorship pods before the music, medics at the gate (Moyo Response), trees in the ground after. Lesson three: the crowd tells you the truth in real time; no dashboard needed. Founders pay consultants for feedback loops this honest. I get them every Friday on a school field.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Building for young Kenyans? Reply "TOUR" and I will share our playbook one-on-one.

PS — I write one longer, more honest version of these every Sunday: The Sunday Signal. Free at euginemicah.tech.', 'Newsletter: the three business lessons, expanded with tour-stop photos.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-08T04:30:00.000Z', 'tour', 'Receipts Saturday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
Before the music: a room full of teenagers, zero phones,
talking about drugs, sex ed and careers. This is the part nobody films.', 'The mentorship pods are the tour''s engine room. Facilitators like Hype Ola and Khloe Nyarangi run sessions on the things Kenyan classrooms whisper about — substance abuse, digital literacy, life after school. No cameras inside. The deal is honesty for privacy. Then tree planting with Delo Greens, so every school keeps a grove that outlives our visit. THEN the stage. People ask why schools keep inviting us back. It is because we deliver the boring, unfilmable value first and the festival second. Order of operations is a brand strategy.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'What conversation do you wish an adult had had with you at 16? Comments open.', 'Newsletter: inside a pod — anonymised questions students actually asked.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-08T16:00:00.000Z', 'tour', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'I posted about this weeks ago. Here is what I left out.
We built a national youth movement with a truck, a stage,
and the radical idea that talent in a village school counts.', 'Urban Gang Tour takes a full broadcast-grade production INTO schools — Koinange Girls, Loreto Kiambu, Gituamba, Lari Boys next. Mentorship pods in the morning (career, digital literacy, substance abuse — the conversations adults avoid), tree planting with Delo Greens, then the stage: music, dance, spoken word, modelling, public speaking. Winners crowned. Everything feeds Urban News on PPP TV, so a girl who has never left her county performs to the whole country by Friday. That is the whole business model: dignity, plus distribution.

The uncut version lives in The Sunday Signal newsletter.', 'Schools, brands, counties — bookings are open at urbangangtour.co.ke/book.', 'Newsletter: the economics of one tour stop, itemised — what it costs to move culture.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-09T07:00:00.000Z', 'newsletter', 'The Sunday Signal', 'document', 'The Sunday Signal #4 — the week''s best story, told properly.', 'NEWSLETTER ISSUE (long-form, ~800 words). Take this week''s highest-engagement post (check /admin performance log) and expand it 4x: the scene, the numbers, what I got wrong, what you can steal. Structure: cold open (the moment) → context (the road here) → the lesson (one, not five) → receipts (screenshots/photos) → next week''s experiment. Close with: "Forwarded this? Subscribe free at euginemicah.tech — one honest signal a week, no noise."', 'Subscribe free at euginemicah.tech — one honest signal a week.', 'IS the newsletter. Post a 3-line teaser + subscribe link on LinkedIn at 10:00.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-10T06:00:00.000Z', 'review', 'Metrics Loop', 'text', 'DAY 28 METRICS REVIEW — evaluate, kill, scale.', 'Internal review (not for posting). 1) Pull impressions/reactions/comments logged in /admin for the last 14 days. 2) Rank pillars by median engagement. 3) KILL: the weakest recurring format or hook style (lowest quartile twice running). 4) SCALE: double the winning pillar''s bonus-slot share for the next 14 days. 5) Check consistency: any missed days? Fix the cause, not the calendar. 6) Newsletter CTA conversion: if <2% of post viewers subscribe, rewrite the CTA line this sprint.', '', 'Feeds the next 14 days of scheduling decisions.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-11T04:30:00.000Z', 'origin', 'Origin Tuesday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
I walked 15 kilometres to school and showered cold.
Now I complain when the studio AC is too high. Growth is funny like that.', 'Chapter Seventeen of my book is literally titled Fifteen Kilometers and a Cold Shower. I am not romanticising it — walking that far on hunger maths is not character-building, it is a policy failure. But it built a floor under me: no day in a newsroom, no brutal edit, no 4am call time has ever been the hardest thing I have done. When your baseline is that floor, Monday cannot scare you. That is the only privilege poverty ever gave me, and I intend to spend it loudly.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Follow along — I post the unpolished version of the media career every week.', 'Newsletter: baseline theory — why your hardest season becomes your unfair advantage.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-11T16:00:00.000Z', 'media', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
How does a guest end up on national TV?
Someone like me stalks their work for weeks first. Here is the pipeline.', 'I direct guest research and booking for Urban News. The pipeline: scan the culture (campus shows, TikTok, gigs, founders'' launches) → shortlist by story, not clout → pre-interview call where I listen for the one moment they light up → build the rundown around that moment. The guests who kill it are never the most famous. They are the ones with a specific story and receipts. If you want to be booked on any show: stop posting your wins, start posting your process. Bookers can smell a real story through the screen.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Building something in Kenyan culture, music, business or tech? Put your story in my comments. I read them as a booker.', 'Newsletter: "how to get booked" — the checklist producers never publish.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-12T04:30:00.000Z', 'media', 'Control Room Wednesday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
The teleprompter fails more often than you think.
What saves you is never the script. It is the reps.', 'Live TV rule one: the machine will betray you on the worst possible day. Prompter dies, earpiece drops, the package refuses to roll, the guest freezes. The audience should never find out. What fills that silence is everything you did before the red light: the pre-reads, the mock bulletins I performed for my brother as a boy, the two hundred Citizen scripts, teaching Friday-afternoon classes in Kakamega. Composure is not a talent. It is compound interest on unglamorous practice. Deposit daily.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'TV people — drop your best on-air save below. Let us trade war stories.', 'Newsletter: five on-air disasters and the exact recovery moves.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-13T04:30:00.000Z', 'builder', 'Ship Log Thursday', 'photo', 'I posted about this weeks ago. Here is what I left out.
A TV host with 7 live GitHub projects.
Media people underestimate code. Coders underestimate media. I stopped doing both.', 'Auto news station. ProPost. Tawala. The Urban Gang Tour platform — multi-route Next.js, M-Pesa checkout, its own admin control room. Seven live projects, zero CS degree. My unfair advantage is not syntax; it is that ten years of broadcasting taught me exactly what content systems should DO before I wrote a line. The future of media in Africa belongs to people who can hold a mic and a terminal in the same week. Both are just distribution.

The uncut version lives in The Sunday Signal newsletter.', 'The code is public: github.com/eugineous. Star what is useful, fork what is not finished.', 'Newsletter: tour of all seven repos — what each one taught me.', 'draft');
