insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-15T04:30:00.000Z', 'origin', 'Receipts Saturday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
A teacher from Kakamega raised a TV host.
Except the teacher and the TV host are the same person.', 'Before television I stood in front of classrooms. Same job, honestly: hold attention, translate the complicated, care whether the back row got it. When people ask how I read an audience on live TV, the answer is thirty teenagers on a Friday afternoon who would rather be anywhere else. If you can teach form three double-lesson maths after lunch, a national broadcast is a warm bath. Every skill you think is beneath your dream job is secretly training for it.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'What "small" job trained you for the big one? I want the specific skill.', 'Newsletter: the classroom-to-studio skills map, itemised.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-15T16:00:00.000Z', 'book', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'I scored a C at KCSE the year everything fell apart.
The book calls it The Year of the C. It nearly ended me.', 'In Kenya we treat exam grades like verdicts. Mine read: average boy, average future. Nobody grades what was happening around the exam — the funerals, the hunger, the fifteen-kilometre walks. I re-sat life instead of the exam. Radio in Thika. A show nobody heard called The Overview. Campus TV. Citizen. PPP. The C never changed. Everything it predicted did. If an exam once called you average, I need you to hear this from someone on national television weekly: verdicts expire.', 'Share this with one student who thinks their grade is their ceiling.', 'Newsletter: The Year of the C, full chapter + reader replies.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-16T07:00:00.000Z', 'newsletter', 'The Sunday Signal', 'document', 'The Sunday Signal #5 — the week''s best story, told properly.', 'NEWSLETTER ISSUE (long-form, ~800 words). Take this week''s highest-engagement post (check /admin performance log) and expand it 4x: the scene, the numbers, what I got wrong, what you can steal. Structure: cold open (the moment) → context (the road here) → the lesson (one, not five) → receipts (screenshots/photos) → next week''s experiment. Close with: "Forwarded this? Subscribe free at euginemicah.tech — one honest signal a week, no noise."', 'Subscribe free at euginemicah.tech — one honest signal a week.', 'IS the newsletter. Post a 3-line teaser + subscribe link on LinkedIn at 10:00.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-17T04:30:00.000Z', 'book', 'Broke Chronicles Monday', 'text', 'Burnout in expensive shoes is still burnout.
I wrote that chapter from experience, not research.', 'The fame did not fix me. That is a whole chapter — Chapter Forty — and it is the one readers message me about at 2am. I got the screen, the recognition, the shoes, and discovered the boy from Lugari had followed me into every studio, still asking if we were safe yet. Success does not silence the old alarm system. It just gives it better acoustics. I manage it now with work as armor — another chapter — but managed is not cured, and I would rather tell you the truth than sell you an arc.', 'If you are winning in public and tired in private, the book was written for you.', 'Newsletter: mental health issue — Fame That Did Not Fix Me + Kenyan men and silence.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-08-18T04:30:00.000Z', 'origin', 'Origin Tuesday', 'text', 'I posted about this weeks ago. Here is what I left out.
From watching CNN on a neighbour''s TV in Lugari
to co-hosting national television. Here is the actual path, no montage.', 'Around 2013 my father had one rule: before he left for the mines each morning, my brother and I watched the news. Not cartoons — CNN, Al Jazeera, France 24. I studied anchors the way other kids studied footballers. Then: village school, township years, a library that did not judge my grammar, Thika radio, campus TV, Citizen TV newsroom, and now Urban News on PPP TV — 2M+ weekly viewers on StarTimes Ch 430. Twelve years between the neighbour''s TV and my own studio chair. The montage version skips eleven of them.

The uncut version lives in The Sunday Signal newsletter.', 'Ask me anything about the path — I answer every serious question in the comments.', 'Newsletter: the full timeline with photos and what each stop actually paid.', 'draft');
