insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-14T04:30:00.000Z', 'book', 'Broke Chronicles Monday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
A white American Quaker sits in my family tree.
David Zarembka. He built me on purpose, in the dark, without applause.', 'People hear "raised by an American" and imagine money. It was not money. It was structure. It was a man who treated a boy in a mud house like a project worth finishing. Between him, a pastor, and a king who named his own hill, I was assembled by a committee nobody paid. The book calls them the ones who stayed after the funerals. Every builder I know has a committee like this. We just do not thank them in public enough.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Tag someone who built you before you were worth building. Let them see it.', 'Newsletter: full Zarembka chapter excerpt + how to be someone''s committee.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-15T04:30:00.000Z', 'origin', 'Origin Tuesday', 'text', 'Reposting this for everyone who joined recently — updated with what changed.
I walked 15 kilometres to school and showered cold.
Now I complain when the studio AC is too high. Growth is funny like that.', 'Chapter Seventeen of my book is literally titled Fifteen Kilometers and a Cold Shower. I am not romanticising it — walking that far on hunger maths is not character-building, it is a policy failure. But it built a floor under me: no day in a newsroom, no brutal edit, no 4am call time has ever been the hardest thing I have done. When your baseline is that floor, Monday cannot scare you. That is the only privilege poverty ever gave me, and I intend to spend it loudly.', 'Follow along — I post the unpolished version of the media career every week.', 'Newsletter: baseline theory — why your hardest season becomes your unfair advantage.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-15T16:00:00.000Z', 'media', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'Reposting this for everyone who joined recently — updated with what changed.
How does a guest end up on national TV?
Someone like me stalks their work for weeks first. Here is the pipeline.', 'I direct guest research and booking for Urban News. The pipeline: scan the culture (campus shows, TikTok, gigs, founders'' launches) → shortlist by story, not clout → pre-interview call where I listen for the one moment they light up → build the rundown around that moment. The guests who kill it are never the most famous. They are the ones with a specific story and receipts. If you want to be booked on any show: stop posting your wins, start posting your process. Bookers can smell a real story through the screen.', 'Building something in Kenyan culture, music, business or tech? Put your story in my comments. I read them as a booker.', 'Newsletter: "how to get booked" — the checklist producers never publish.', 'draft');
