My brother Dante was my first audience.
He heard every broadcast I ever gave — years before a camera did.', 'Before Citizen TV, before Urban News, before 2M viewers, there was a boy performing news bulletins to his brother in a mud house in Lugari. I interviewed chickens. I reported droughts from the doorway. Dante clapped anyway. Here is what I know about audiences now that I did not know then: the size never mattered. The habit did. I practised being watchable for a decade before anyone watched. That is the part the overnight-success story always deletes.

