insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-22T16:00:00.000Z', 'tour', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'I posted about this weeks ago. Here is what I left out.
A student who had never held a mic opened for 3,000 people.
What building a youth movement teaches you about business:', 'Everything I know about product-market fit I learned watching a school field at 7am become a festival by noon. Lesson one: distribution beats talent alone — the stage matters because PPP TV cameras are on it. Lesson two: trust is the moat — teachers let us in because we run mentorship pods before the music, medics at the gate (Moyo Response), trees in the ground after. Lesson three: the crowd tells you the truth in real time; no dashboard needed. Founders pay consultants for feedback loops this honest. I get them every Friday on a school field.

The uncut version lives in The Sunday Signal newsletter.', 'Building for young Kenyans? Reply "TOUR" and I will share our playbook one-on-one.', 'Newsletter: the three business lessons, expanded with tour-stop photos.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-23T04:30:00.000Z', 'media', 'Control Room Wednesday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
What 2 million weekly viewers actually looks like from inside the studio:
a countdown, a dry mouth, and a co-host who has your back.', 'Urban News, PPP TV, StarTimes Ch 430. People imagine glamour. Here is the real inventory: guest research files at midnight, a rundown that changes twice before air, the floor manager''s fingers counting you in, and Lucy Ogunde beside me running the same high-wire act. Co-hosting looks like friendship to the audience and feels like trapeze work to us — you learn to catch each other mid-sentence. TV is a team sport wearing an individual''s face. Anyone selling you the solo-genius version has never been in a control room.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Want the full behind-the-scenes? The Sunday Signal newsletter goes deeper every week — link in profile.', 'Newsletter: anatomy of one episode, from rundown to wrap.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-24T04:30:00.000Z', 'builder', 'Ship Log Thursday', 'photo', 'I posted about this weeks ago. Here is what I left out.
A TV host with 7 live GitHub projects.
Media people underestimate code. Coders underestimate media. I stopped doing both.', 'Auto news station. ProPost. Tawala. The Urban Gang Tour platform — multi-route Next.js, M-Pesa checkout, its own admin control room. Seven live projects, zero CS degree. My unfair advantage is not syntax; it is that ten years of broadcasting taught me exactly what content systems should DO before I wrote a line. The future of media in Africa belongs to people who can hold a mic and a terminal in the same week. Both are just distribution.

The uncut version lives in The Sunday Signal newsletter.', 'The code is public: github.com/eugineous. Star what is useful, fork what is not finished.', 'Newsletter: tour of all seven repos — what each one taught me.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-25T04:30:00.000Z', 'tour', 'Tour Diary Friday', 'text', 'I posted about this weeks ago. Here is what I left out.
Before the music: a room full of teenagers, zero phones,
talking about drugs, sex ed and careers. This is the part nobody films.', 'The mentorship pods are the tour''s engine room. Facilitators like Hype Ola and Khloe Nyarangi run sessions on the things Kenyan classrooms whisper about — substance abuse, digital literacy, life after school. No cameras inside. The deal is honesty for privacy. Then tree planting with Delo Greens, so every school keeps a grove that outlives our visit. THEN the stage. People ask why schools keep inviting us back. It is because we deliver the boring, unfilmable value first and the festival second. Order of operations is a brand strategy.

The uncut version lives in The Sunday Signal newsletter.', 'What conversation do you wish an adult had had with you at 16? Comments open.

PS — I write one longer, more honest version of these every Sunday: The Sunday Signal. Free at euginemicah.tech.', 'Newsletter: inside a pod — anonymised questions students actually asked.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-26T04:30:00.000Z', 'book', 'Receipts Saturday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
I scored a C at KCSE the year everything fell apart.
The book calls it The Year of the C. It nearly ended me.', 'In Kenya we treat exam grades like verdicts. Mine read: average boy, average future. Nobody grades what was happening around the exam — the funerals, the hunger, the fifteen-kilometre walks. I re-sat life instead of the exam. Radio in Thika. A show nobody heard called The Overview. Campus TV. Citizen. PPP. The C never changed. Everything it predicted did. If an exam once called you average, I need you to hear this from someone on national television weekly: verdicts expire.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Share this with one student who thinks their grade is their ceiling.', 'Newsletter: The Year of the C, full chapter + reader replies.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-26T16:00:00.000Z', 'builder', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'I posted about this weeks ago. Here is what I left out.
I automated PPP TV''s news-to-social pipeline.
One broadcast now becomes 20 assets before the anchors leave the building.', 'The problem: brilliant TV segments dying at 9pm because nobody had bandwidth to cut, caption and post them. The build: an automated pipeline that takes broadcast output and turns it into platform-native clips and posts — part of how the channel grew past 700K YouTube subscribers. The lesson for every media house on this continent: your archive is not storage, it is inventory. If a Lugari boy can wire this together with open tools, your organisation can. The gap is not budget. It is permission to try.

The uncut version lives in The Sunday Signal newsletter.', 'Media managers: DM me "PIPELINE" and I will send the plain-English architecture.', 'Newsletter: the pipeline post-mortem — costs, tools, what broke.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-27T07:00:00.000Z', 'newsletter', 'The Sunday Signal', 'document', 'The Sunday Signal #11 — the week''s best story, told properly.', 'NEWSLETTER ISSUE (long-form, ~800 words). Take this week''s highest-engagement post (check /admin performance log) and expand it 4x: the scene, the numbers, what I got wrong, what you can steal. Structure: cold open (the moment) → context (the road here) → the lesson (one, not five) → receipts (screenshots/photos) → next week''s experiment. Close with: "Forwarded this? Subscribe free at euginemicah.tech — one honest signal a week, no noise."', 'Subscribe free at euginemicah.tech — one honest signal a week.', 'IS the newsletter. Post a 3-line teaser + subscribe link on LinkedIn at 10:00.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-28T04:30:00.000Z', 'book', 'Broke Chronicles Monday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
Burnout in expensive shoes is still burnout.
I wrote that chapter from experience, not research.', 'The fame did not fix me. That is a whole chapter — Chapter Forty — and it is the one readers message me about at 2am. I got the screen, the recognition, the shoes, and discovered the boy from Lugari had followed me into every studio, still asking if we were safe yet. Success does not silence the old alarm system. It just gives it better acoustics. I manage it now with work as armor — another chapter — but managed is not cured, and I would rather tell you the truth than sell you an arc.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'If you are winning in public and tired in private, the book was written for you.', 'Newsletter: mental health issue — Fame That Did Not Fix Me + Kenyan men and silence.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-29T04:30:00.000Z', 'origin', 'Origin Tuesday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
The library did not judge my grammar.
That is why I still write like a man who owes libraries money.', 'Township years. I was the boy reading borrowed books with red dust still on his ankles. My English arrived second-hand and I wore it anyway. Today I have filed 200+ bilingual stories for a national newsroom and co-host a show in the language that library lent me. When people polish their story until the struggle disappears, the algorithm may clap but nobody is helped. Rough drafts inspire more than final edits. Post yours.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'What did a library, a teacher, or one free resource unlock for you?', 'Newsletter: "second-hand English" — language, class and Kenyan media.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-29T16:00:00.000Z', 'book', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'I posted about this weeks ago. Here is what I left out.
My first crime was committed from inside my mother.
She crossed a border pregnant with me. I was contraband before I was a person.', 'That is the first line of my memoir because it is the truest one. Born Broke, Built Loud is not a success story — I say that on page one. It is a field report from the middle of the climb. My mother survived on sugar water and faith. My father fainted over me before he ever held me. A stranger named Hassan Omar once handed me twenty five shillings and, without knowing it, kept me in school. Twenty five bob. That is how thin the line was between the man typing this and nobody.

The uncut version lives in The Sunday Signal newsletter.', 'The book is called Born Broke, Built Loud. Chapter one is free on my site — euginemicah.tech/book.', 'Newsletter: expand into the full smuggling story + why I opened the book with a confession.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-09-30T04:30:00.000Z', 'media', 'Control Room Wednesday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
I wrote 200+ stories at Citizen TV before anyone knew my face.
The invisible reps are the ones that count.', 'Walking into Royal Media Services as a young reporter felt like entering a temple. Nobody hands you an anchor chair there. They hand you deadlines — bilingual, daily, unforgiving. Two hundred plus stories taught me what no masterclass sells: how to find the human in a budget report, how to cut a script by half without losing the truth, how to file clean when the bus was late and the source lied. Every visible minute I get on PPP TV was purchased with those invisible hours. Pay for yours early.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Journalists and creators: what were your invisible reps? Normalise naming them.', 'Newsletter: the Citizen years — three stories that taught me the craft.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-10-01T04:30:00.000Z', 'builder', 'Ship Log Thursday', 'photo', 'Reposting this for everyone who joined recently — updated with what changed.
I built an AI system with 150+ agents that posts content while I sleep.
Here is ProPost, receipts included.', 'ProPost runs 150+ AI agents that draft, schedule and publish across platforms — built nights and weekends around a daily TV job, on Next.js, Supabase and Cloudflare Workers, wired into the Meta Graph API. Not a demo: it has been running my pipelines for months. The insight that unlocked it: agents fail alone but work in assembly lines — one researches, one drafts, one fact-checks, one schedules. Same as a newsroom. I did not invent a workflow; I automated the one I already lived in. Your industry knowledge IS your AI advantage. Automate what you uniquely understand.', 'Want the architecture breakdown? Ship Log Thursday, every week. Follow so you do not miss it.', 'Newsletter: ProPost architecture diagram + the three failed versions before it.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-10-02T04:30:00.000Z', 'tour', 'Tour Diary Friday', 'text', 'Reposting this for everyone who joined recently — updated with what changed.
We built a national youth movement with a truck, a stage,
and the radical idea that talent in a village school counts.', 'Urban Gang Tour takes a full broadcast-grade production INTO schools — Koinange Girls, Loreto Kiambu, Gituamba, Lari Boys next. Mentorship pods in the morning (career, digital literacy, substance abuse — the conversations adults avoid), tree planting with Delo Greens, then the stage: music, dance, spoken word, modelling, public speaking. Winners crowned. Everything feeds Urban News on PPP TV, so a girl who has never left her county performs to the whole country by Friday. That is the whole business model: dignity, plus distribution.', 'Schools, brands, counties — bookings are open at urbangangtour.co.ke/book.

PS — I write one longer, more honest version of these every Sunday: The Sunday Signal. Free at euginemicah.tech.', 'Newsletter: the economics of one tour stop, itemised — what it costs to move culture.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-10-03T04:30:00.000Z', 'media', 'Receipts Saturday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
How does a guest end up on national TV?
Someone like me stalks their work for weeks first. Here is the pipeline.', 'I direct guest research and booking for Urban News. The pipeline: scan the culture (campus shows, TikTok, gigs, founders'' launches) → shortlist by story, not clout → pre-interview call where I listen for the one moment they light up → build the rundown around that moment. The guests who kill it are never the most famous. They are the ones with a specific story and receipts. If you want to be booked on any show: stop posting your wins, start posting your process. Bookers can smell a real story through the screen.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Building something in Kenyan culture, music, business or tech? Put your story in my comments. I read them as a booker.', 'Newsletter: "how to get booked" — the checklist producers never publish.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-10-03T16:00:00.000Z', 'origin', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
I walked 15 kilometres to school and showered cold.
Now I complain when the studio AC is too high. Growth is funny like that.', 'Chapter Seventeen of my book is literally titled Fifteen Kilometers and a Cold Shower. I am not romanticising it — walking that far on hunger maths is not character-building, it is a policy failure. But it built a floor under me: no day in a newsroom, no brutal edit, no 4am call time has ever been the hardest thing I have done. When your baseline is that floor, Monday cannot scare you. That is the only privilege poverty ever gave me, and I intend to spend it loudly.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'Follow along — I post the unpolished version of the media career every week.', 'Newsletter: baseline theory — why your hardest season becomes your unfair advantage.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-10-04T07:00:00.000Z', 'newsletter', 'The Sunday Signal', 'document', 'The Sunday Signal #12 — the week''s best story, told properly.', 'NEWSLETTER ISSUE (long-form, ~800 words). Take this week''s highest-engagement post (check /admin performance log) and expand it 4x: the scene, the numbers, what I got wrong, what you can steal. Structure: cold open (the moment) → context (the road here) → the lesson (one, not five) → receipts (screenshots/photos) → next week''s experiment. Close with: "Forwarded this? Subscribe free at euginemicah.tech — one honest signal a week, no noise."', 'Subscribe free at euginemicah.tech — one honest signal a week.', 'IS the newsletter. Post a 3-line teaser + subscribe link on LinkedIn at 10:00.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-10-05T06:00:00.000Z', 'review', 'Metrics Loop', 'text', 'DAY 84 METRICS REVIEW — evaluate, kill, scale.', 'Internal review (not for posting). 1) Pull impressions/reactions/comments logged in /admin for the last 14 days. 2) Rank pillars by median engagement. 3) KILL: the weakest recurring format or hook style (lowest quartile twice running). 4) SCALE: double the winning pillar''s bonus-slot share for the next 14 days. 5) Check consistency: any missed days? Fix the cause, not the calendar. 6) Newsletter CTA conversion: if <2% of post viewers subscribe, rewrite the CTA line this sprint.', '', 'Feeds the next 14 days of scheduling decisions.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-10-06T04:30:00.000Z', 'origin', 'Origin Tuesday', 'text', 'Part two of a story many of you asked about.
A teacher from Kakamega raised a TV host.
Except the teacher and the TV host are the same person.', 'Before television I stood in front of classrooms. Same job, honestly: hold attention, translate the complicated, care whether the back row got it. When people ask how I read an audience on live TV, the answer is thirty teenagers on a Friday afternoon who would rather be anywhere else. If you can teach form three double-lesson maths after lunch, a national broadcast is a warm bath. Every skill you think is beneath your dream job is secretly training for it.

If you missed part one, it is pinned on my profile.', 'What "small" job trained you for the big one? I want the specific skill.', 'Newsletter: the classroom-to-studio skills map, itemised.', 'draft');
insert into posts (scheduled_at, pillar, series, format, hook, body, cta, repurpose, status) values ('2026-10-06T16:00:00.000Z', 'builder', 'Bonus Slot', 'text', 'Reposting this for everyone who joined recently — updated with what changed.
